# AI Development Rules for Claude Code

## Core Principles

### 1. Test-Driven Development (MANDATORY)
- **ALWAYS update tests IMMEDIATELY after fixing a bug**
- **ALWAYS run ALL tests after EVERY fix**
- Never claim a fix is complete without running tests
- Integration tests must validate real-world behavior, not just happy paths

### 2. Trust Building Through Verification
- Don't just write code - VERIFY it works
- If you make a claim (e.g., "this fixes the issue"), PROVE it with test output
- Run tests before presenting solutions to the user
- If tests fail, fix and rerun - don't present failures

### 3. Test Coverage Requirements
When creating a new feature:
1. Write unit tests (logic validation)
2. Write integration tests (end-to-end validation)
3. Run ALL tests before marking work complete
4. Update tests when bugs are discovered
5. Rerun ALL tests after fixing bugs

### 4. Debugging Workflow
When a bug is reported:
1. Add debug logging to understand the issue
2. Create a test that reproduces the bug
3. Fix the bug
4. Update ALL related tests
5. Run ALL tests (unit + integration)
6. Only then report the fix to the user

### 5. Communication Standards
- Don't tell the user to test manually - YOU test first
- Show test results as proof of fixes
- Be honest about failures - don't hide them
- If something doesn't work, say so immediately

### 6. Code Quality Standards
- Don't use deprecated APIs (e.g., ScriptProcessorNode)
- Validate buffer sizes and data formats
- Add proper error handling
- Include debug logging for critical paths

## Project-Specific Rules

### GTranslate V4
- Audio chunks must be 8192 bytes (4096 samples × 2 bytes)
- Always verify Google Cloud API integration
- Test with real audio streaming scenarios
- Validate both interim and final results
- Check server logs for errors

## Test Files
- `test-streaming-speech.js` - Unit tests (12 tests)
- `test-integration.js` - Integration tests (9 tests)
- Run both test suites after every change

## Never Do This
❌ Fix code without updating tests
❌ Update tests without running them
❌ Tell user "it should work now" without proof
❌ Skip integration tests
❌ Ignore failed tests

## Always Do This
✅ Update tests immediately after bug fixes
✅ Run ALL tests after EVERY change
✅ Show test results to user
✅ Add new tests for new bugs discovered
✅ Verify fixes work in real scenarios
